<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-11T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-11T19:00:00-05:00" n="732" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/2–947: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the British Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bevin</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d732fn1">Sent to London as Department telegram 697, with the
                                instruction: “Please deliver to Mr. Bevin the following message from
                                the Secretary.”</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-11T19:00:00-05:00">February
                                    11, 1947—7 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I am sending you this interim line to thank you for your most helpful
                            explanatory message on your recent Palestine proposals. I am glad that
                            you found my remarks to the press helpful. I was most anxious not to
                            embarrass you in your difficult and delicate task. I am studying the
                            proposals and if questions occur to me to which I cannot get answers
                            here I may bother you with them.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>